I. TERMS
The Licensor hereby grants you the right to copy, modify, create derivative 
works, redistribute, and make non-production use of the Licensed Work. 
The Licensor may make an Additional Use Grant, above, permitting limited 
production use.

II. ADDITIONAL USE GRANT
Production use is permitted ONLY if the User meets one of the following conditions:

1. FREE TIER: The User is an individual, registered non-profit organization 
   (501(c)(3) or equivalent), registered not-for-profit organization, or 
   for-profit entity with total annual gross revenue of less than $1,000,000 USD. 
   
   FREE TIER RESTRICTIONS: Free Tier users may use the Licensed Work for their 
   own internal operations only. Offering the Licensed Work (or products 
   substantially based on it) to third parties, whether as a service or as a 
   distributable product, requires an OEM License regardless of whether such 
   offering is free or paid.
   
   No registration or license agreement required for internal use.

2. COMMERCIAL TIER: The User has entered into a separate written Commercial 
   License Agreement with Licensor. (Standard pricing: $5,000 USD per 
   production site per year, applicable to entities with revenue between 
   $1,000,000 and $100,000,000 USD).

3. ENTERPRISE TIER: The User has entered into a separate written Enterprise 
   License Agreement with Licensor (required for entities with revenue 
   exceeding $100,000,000 USD).

4. OEM/MANAGED SERVICE: The User has entered into a separate written OEM 
   License Agreement with Licensor. Required for:
   
   a) Offering the Licensed Work as a hosted or managed service to third parties
   b) Distributing the Licensed Work or products substantially based on it to 
      third parties (whether open source, proprietary, free, or paid)
   c) Embedding the Licensed Work in products offered to third parties
   
   NOTE: Non-profit and not-for-profit organizations requiring OEM licenses 
   for third-party offerings may contact sales@kernx.io for case-by-case 
   evaluation and pricing.

Any production use by entities not meeting the Free Tier criteria requires 
a valid commercial license.

III. DEFINITIONS
- "Production" means running the Licensed Work where it serves real user 
  traffic, handles financial data, or supports business operations.

- "Production Site" means a single logical deployment of the Licensed Work, 
  regardless of the number of servers or instances. Multiple data centers 
  or regions operated by the same entity count as separate sites.

- "Licensor" means Siva (via Kernx.io).

